{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1480,"text":"I thought I would start\nwith a very brief history of cities."},{"time":6040,"text":"Settlements typically began\nwith people clustered around a well,"},{"time":10640,"text":"and the size of that settlement\nwas roughly the distance you could walk"},{"time":13998,"text":"with a pot of water on your head."},{"time":15960,"text":"In fact, if you fly\nover Germany, for example,"},{"time":19480,"text":"and you look down and you see\nthese hundreds of little villages,"},{"time":22504,"text":"they're all about a mile apart."},{"time":24264,"text":"You needed easy access to the fields."},{"time":27080,"text":"And for hundreds, even thousands of years,"},{"time":30480,"text":"the home was really the center of life."},{"time":33080,"text":"Life was very small for most people."},{"time":35680,"text":"It was a center of entertainment,\nof energy production, of work,"},{"time":41800,"text":"a center of health care."},{"time":43040,"text":"That's where babies were born\nand people died."}]},{"cues":[{"time":46360,"text":"Then, with industrialization,\neverything started to become centralized."},{"time":51240,"text":"You had dirty factories that were moved\nto the outskirts of cities."},{"time":55280,"text":"Production was centralized\nin assembly plants."},{"time":59640,"text":"You had centralized energy production."},{"time":63240,"text":"Learning took place in schools."},{"time":64959,"text":"Health care took place in hospitals."},{"time":69000,"text":"And then you had networks that developed."},{"time":71040,"text":"You had water, sewer networks"},{"time":73680,"text":"that allowed for this\nkind of unchecked expansion."},{"time":77560,"text":"You had separated functions, increasingly."},{"time":81200,"text":"You had rail networks"},{"time":82960,"text":"that connected residential,\nindustrial, commercial areas."},{"time":85800,"text":"You had auto networks."},{"time":87440,"text":"In fact, the model was really,\ngive everybody a car,"},{"time":90720,"text":"build roads to everything,"},{"time":92080,"text":"and give people a place to park\nwhen they get there."},{"time":94560,"text":"It was not a very functional model."},{"time":96280,"text":"And we still live in that world,"},{"time":98680,"text":"and this is what we end up with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":100840,"text":"So you have the sprawl of LA,"},{"time":102920,"text":"the sprawl of Mexico City."},{"time":105120,"text":"You have these unbelievable\nnew cities in China,"},{"time":108240,"text":"which you might call tower sprawl."},{"time":110600,"text":"They're all building cities"},{"time":111960,"text":"on the model that we invented\nin the '50s and '60s,"},{"time":114920,"text":"which is really obsolete, I would argue,"},{"time":116960,"text":"and there are hundreds\nand hundreds of new cities"},{"time":119270,"text":"that are being planned all over the world."},{"time":121350,"text":"In China alone, 300 million people,\nsome say 400 million people,"},{"time":125400,"text":"will move to the city\nover the next 15 years."},{"time":127760,"text":"That means building the equivalent"},{"time":130280,"text":"of the entire built infrastructure\nof the US in 15 years."},{"time":133120,"text":"Imagine that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":134360,"text":"And we should all care about this\nwhether you live in cities or not."},{"time":139040,"text":"Cities will account for 90 percent\nof the population growth,"},{"time":142640,"text":"80 percent of the global CO2,\n75 percent of energy use,"},{"time":147440,"text":"but at the same time\nit's where people want to be,"},{"time":149960,"text":"increasingly."},{"time":151560,"text":"More than half the people\nnow in the world live in cities,"},{"time":154400,"text":"and that will just continue to escalate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":157120,"text":"Cities are places of celebration,\npersonal expression."},{"time":160760,"text":"You have the flash mobs\nof pillow fights that --"},{"time":164080,"text":"I've been to a couple. They're quite fun."},{"time":166200,"text":"You have --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":167440,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":168720,"text":"Cities are where most\nof the wealth is created,"},{"time":171560,"text":"and particularly in the developing world,\nit's where women find opportunities."},{"time":175280,"text":"That's a lot of the reason\nwhy cities are growing very quickly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":178720,"text":"Now there's some trends\nthat will impact cities."},{"time":181360,"text":"First of all, work is becoming\ndistributed and mobile."},{"time":184280,"text":"The office building is basically obsolete\nfor doing private work."},{"time":187920,"text":"The home, once again,\nbecause of distributed computation --"},{"time":192320,"text":"Communication is becoming\na center of life,"},{"time":194360,"text":"so it's a center of production\nand learning and shopping and health care"},{"time":198560,"text":"and all of these things\nthat we used to think of"},{"time":201360,"text":"as taking place outside of the home."}]},{"cues":[{"time":204200,"text":"And increasingly,\neverything that people buy,"},{"time":207200,"text":"every consumer product,"},{"time":208560,"text":"in one way or another,\ncan be personalized."},{"time":211520,"text":"And that's a very important\ntrend to think about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213960,"text":"So this is my image\nof the city of the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":217059,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":219440,"text":"In that it's a place for people, you know."},{"time":221720,"text":"Maybe not the way people dress, but --"},{"time":224440,"text":"You know, the question now is,"},{"time":225893,"text":"how can we have all the good things\nthat we identify with cities"},{"time":229360,"text":"without all the bad things?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":231200,"text":"This is Bangalore."},{"time":232440,"text":"It took me a couple of hours\nto get a few miles in Bangalore last year."},{"time":236520,"text":"So with cities, you also have\ncongestion and pollution"},{"time":239080,"text":"and disease and all these negative things."},{"time":241760,"text":"How can we have the good stuff\nwithout the bad?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":244000,"text":"So we went back and started looking\nat the great cities"},{"time":246596,"text":"that evolved before the cars."},{"time":248720,"text":"Paris was a series of these\nlittle villages that came together,"},{"time":253080,"text":"and you still see that structure today."},{"time":255000,"text":"The 20 arrondissements of Paris\nare these little neighborhoods."},{"time":257977,"text":"Most of what people need in life\ncan be within a five- or 10-minute walk."},{"time":262720,"text":"And if you look at the data,\nwhen you have that kind of a structure,"},{"time":265960,"text":"you get a very even distribution"},{"time":267680,"text":"of the shops and the physicians\nand the pharmacies"},{"time":271080,"text":"and the cafes in Paris."},{"time":273000,"text":"And then you look at cities\nthat evolved after the automobile,"},{"time":275960,"text":"and it's not that kind of a pattern."},{"time":277720,"text":"There's very little\nthat's within a five-minute walk"},{"time":280760,"text":"of most areas of places like Pittsburgh."},{"time":283080,"text":"Not to pick on Pittsburgh,"},{"time":284360,"text":"but most American cities\nreally have evolved this way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288920,"text":"So we said, well,\nlet's look at new cities,"},{"time":291120,"text":"and we're involved in a couple\nof new city projects in China."},{"time":295360,"text":"So we said, let's start\nwith that neighborhood cell."},{"time":297840,"text":"We think of it as a compact urban cell."},{"time":299760,"text":"So provide most of what most people want\nwithin that 20-minute walk."},{"time":303360,"text":"This can also be\na resilient electrical microgrid,"},{"time":306920,"text":"community heating, power,\ncommunication networks, etc."},{"time":310520,"text":"can be concentrated there."},{"time":312320,"text":"Stewart Brand would put\na micronuclear reactor"},{"time":315200,"text":"right in the center, probably."},{"time":317200,"text":"And he might be right."},{"time":318680,"text":"And then we can form,\nin effect, a mesh network."},{"time":322240,"text":"It's something of an Internet\ntypology pattern,"},{"time":325880,"text":"so you can have a series\nof these neighborhoods."},{"time":328400,"text":"You can dial up the density --"},{"time":329880,"text":"about 20,000 people per cell,\nif it's Cambridge."},{"time":332400,"text":"Go up to 50,000 if it's Manhattan density."},{"time":334960,"text":"You connect everything with mass transit"},{"time":337080,"text":"and you provide most of what most people\nneed within that neighborhood."},{"time":341360,"text":"You can begin to develop\na whole typology of streetscapes"},{"time":344600,"text":"and the vehicles that can go on them."},{"time":347680,"text":"I won't go through all of them.\nI'll just show one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":350120,"text":"This is Boulder. It's a great example\nof kind of a mobility parkway,"},{"time":354040,"text":"a superhighway for joggers and bicyclists,"},{"time":356800,"text":"where you can go from one end\nof the city to the other"},{"time":359348,"text":"without crossing the street,"},{"time":361120,"text":"and they also have bike-sharing,\nwhich I'll get into in a minute."}]},{"cues":[{"time":364920,"text":"This is even a more interesting solution"},{"time":367120,"text":"in Seoul, Korea."},{"time":368360,"text":"They took the elevated highway,\nthey got rid of it,"},{"time":370800,"text":"they reclaimed the street,\nthe river down below,"},{"time":374440,"text":"below the street,"},{"time":375840,"text":"and you can go from one end\nof Seoul to the other"},{"time":378200,"text":"without crossing a pathway for cars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381880,"text":"The High Line in Manhattan\nis very similar."},{"time":386360,"text":"You have these rapidly emerging\nbike lanes all over the world."},{"time":390560,"text":"I lived in Manhattan for 15 years."},{"time":392240,"text":"I went back a couple of weekends ago,"},{"time":394520,"text":"took this photograph of these fabulous\nnew bike lanes that they have installed."},{"time":400120,"text":"They're still not to where Copenhagen is,"},{"time":402960,"text":"where something like 42 percent\nof the trips within the city"},{"time":406400,"text":"are by bicycle."},{"time":407640,"text":"It's mostly just because they have\nfantastic infrastructure there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":411440,"text":"We actually did exactly\nthe wrong thing in Boston."},{"time":414160,"text":"The Big Dig --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":416240,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":418760,"text":"So we got rid of the highway\nbut we created a traffic island,"},{"time":422800,"text":"and it's certainly not a mobility pathway\nfor anything other than cars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":427520,"text":"Mobility on demand is something\nwe've been thinking about,"},{"time":430280,"text":"so we think we need an ecosystem\nof these shared-use vehicles"},{"time":433600,"text":"connected to mass transit."},{"time":435720,"text":"These are some of the vehicles\nthat we've been working on."},{"time":438800,"text":"But shared use is really key."},{"time":440480,"text":"If you share a vehicle, you can have\nat least four people use one vehicle,"},{"time":444400,"text":"as opposed to one."},{"time":446280,"text":"We have Hubway here in Boston,\nthe VÃ©lib' system in Paris."}]},{"cues":[{"time":452760,"text":"We've been developing,\nat the Media Lab, this little city car"},{"time":457040,"text":"that is optimized\nfor shared use in cities."},{"time":460240,"text":"We got rid of all the useless things\nlike engines and transmissions."},{"time":463640,"text":"We moved everything to the wheels,"},{"time":465640,"text":"so you have the drive motor,"},{"time":467040,"text":"the steering motor, the breaking --\nall in the wheel."},{"time":469560,"text":"That left the chassis unencumbered,\nso you can do things like fold,"},{"time":472760,"text":"so you can fold this little vehicle up\nto occupy a tiny little footprint."}]},{"cues":[{"time":478440,"text":"This was a video that was\non European television last week"},{"time":481920,"text":"showing the Spanish Minister of Industry\ndriving this little vehicle,"},{"time":487560,"text":"and when it's folded, it can spin."},{"time":489400,"text":"You don't need reverse.\nYou don't need parallel parking."},{"time":492680,"text":"You just spin and go directly in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":494320,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":495920,"text":"So we've been working\nwith a company to commercialize this."},{"time":498720,"text":"My PhD student Ryan Chin\npresented these early ideas"},{"time":501840,"text":"two years ago at a TEDx conference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":504520,"text":"So what's interesting is,"},{"time":507040,"text":"then if you begin to add\nnew things to it, like autonomy,"},{"time":509880,"text":"you get out of the car,\nyou park at your destination,"},{"time":512679,"text":"you pat it on the butt, it goes\nand it parks itself, it charges itself,"},{"time":516520,"text":"and you can get something\nlike seven times as many vehicles"},{"time":521120,"text":"in a given area as conventional cars,"},{"time":524480,"text":"and we think this is the future."},{"time":526080,"text":"Actually, we could do this today.\nIt's not really a problem."},{"time":529800,"text":"We can combine shared use\nand folding and autonomy"},{"time":533360,"text":"and we get something\nlike 28 times the land utilization"},{"time":536680,"text":"with that kind of strategy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":538360,"text":"One of our graduate students then says,"},{"time":540242,"text":"well, how does a driverless car\ncommunicate with pedestrians?"},{"time":544400,"text":"You have nobody to make eye contact with."},{"time":546600,"text":"You don't know\nif it's going to run you over."},{"time":548760,"text":"So he's developing strategies"},{"time":550360,"text":"so the vehicle can communicate\nwith pedestrians, so --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":552960,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":554400,"text":"So the headlights are eyeballs,\nthe pupils can dilate,"},{"time":557360,"text":"we have directional audio,\nwe can throw sound directly at people."},{"time":561560,"text":"What I love about this project"},{"time":563040,"text":"is he solved a problem\nthat doesn't exist yet, so --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":566680,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":569640,"text":"We also think that we can\ndemocratize access to bike lanes."},{"time":573520,"text":"You know, bike lanes are mostly used\nby young guys in stretchy pants. So --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":577440,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":578840,"text":"We think we can develop a vehicle\nthat operates on bike lanes,"},{"time":582680,"text":"accessible to elderly and disabled,\nwomen in skirts, businesspeople,"},{"time":587680,"text":"and address the issues\nof energy congestion, mobility,"},{"time":590280,"text":"aging and obesity simultaneously."},{"time":592560,"text":"That's our challenge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":593800,"text":"This is an early design\nfor this little three-wheel."},{"time":596680,"text":"It's an electronic bike."},{"time":598200,"text":"You have to pedal\nto operate it in a bike lane,"},{"time":601960,"text":"but if you're an older person,\nthat's a switch."},{"time":604600,"text":"If you're a healthy person, you might\nhave to work really hard to go fast."},{"time":608400,"text":"You can dial in 40 calories\ngoing into work"},{"time":610720,"text":"and 500 going home,\nwhen you can take a shower."},{"time":613400,"text":"We hope to have that built this fall."}]},{"cues":[{"time":617680,"text":"Housing is another area\nwhere we can really improve."},{"time":621080,"text":"Mayor Menino in Boston says"},{"time":623280,"text":"lack of affordable housing\nfor young people"},{"time":626240,"text":"is one of the biggest\nproblems the city faces."},{"time":629000,"text":"Developers say, OK,\nwe'll build little teeny apartments."},{"time":631760,"text":"People say, we don't really want to live\nin a little teeny conventional apartment."},{"time":636040,"text":"So we're saying, let's build\na standardized chassis,"},{"time":640120,"text":"much like our car."},{"time":641480,"text":"Let's bring advanced technology\ninto the apartment,"},{"time":646600,"text":"technology-enabled infill,"},{"time":649160,"text":"give people the tools\nwithin this open-loft chassis"},{"time":654160,"text":"to go through a process of defining"},{"time":656000,"text":"what their needs\nand values and activities are,"},{"time":658960,"text":"and then a matching algorithm\nwill match a unique assembly"},{"time":662560,"text":"of integrated infill components,"},{"time":664560,"text":"furniture, and cabinetry,\nthat are personalized to that individual,"},{"time":669680,"text":"and they give them the tools"},{"time":671080,"text":"to go through the process\nand to refine it,"},{"time":673120,"text":"and it's something like working\nwith an architect,"},{"time":675520,"text":"where the dialogue starts"},{"time":676800,"text":"when you give an alternative\nto a person to react to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":682800,"text":"Now, the most interesting\nimplementation of that for us"},{"time":687520,"text":"is when you can begin\nto have robotic walls,"},{"time":689600,"text":"so your space can convert\nfrom exercise to a workplace,"},{"time":693440,"text":"if you run a virtual company."},{"time":695200,"text":"You have guests over,"},{"time":696374,"text":"you have two guest rooms\nthat are developed."},{"time":700080,"text":"You have a conventional\none-bedroom arrangement"},{"time":703960,"text":"when you need it."},{"time":705188,"text":"Maybe that's most of the time."},{"time":706740,"text":"You have a dinner party."},{"time":707920,"text":"The table folds out to fit 16 people\nin otherwise a conventional one-bedroom,"},{"time":712000,"text":"or maybe you want a dance studio."},{"time":713640,"text":"I mean, architects have been thinking\nabout these ideas for a long time."},{"time":717080,"text":"What we need to do now,"},{"time":719320,"text":"develop things that can scale\nto those 300 million Chinese people"},{"time":724840,"text":"that would like to live in the city,\nand very comfortably."},{"time":729000,"text":"We think we can make\na very small apartment"},{"time":731320,"text":"that functions as if it's twice as big\nby utilizing these strategies."},{"time":736680,"text":"I don't believe in smart homes.\nThat's sort of a bogus concept."},{"time":740240,"text":"I think you have to build dumb homes\nand put smart stuff in it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":743480,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":745760,"text":"And so we've been working\non a chassis of the wall itself."},{"time":751200,"text":"You know, standardized platform"},{"time":752760,"text":"with the motors and the battery\nwhen it operates,"},{"time":755560,"text":"little solenoids that will lock it\nin place and get low-voltage power."},{"time":760120,"text":"We think this can all be standardized,"},{"time":761960,"text":"and then people can personalize the stuff\nthat goes into that wall,"},{"time":765920,"text":"and like the car, we can integrate\nall kinds of sensing"},{"time":768640,"text":"to be aware of human activity,"},{"time":771040,"text":"so if there's a baby\nor a puppy in the way,"},{"time":774360,"text":"you won't have a problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":775600,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":776640,"text":"So the developers say,\nwell, this is great."},{"time":779400,"text":"OK, so if we have a conventional building,\nwe have a fixed envelope,"},{"time":783480,"text":"maybe we can put in 14 units."},{"time":785560,"text":"If they function\nas if they're twice as big,"},{"time":787680,"text":"we can get 28 units in."},{"time":789240,"text":"That means twice as much parking, though."},{"time":791289,"text":"Parking's really expensive."},{"time":792620,"text":"It's about 70,000 dollars per space"},{"time":795280,"text":"to build a conventional parking spot\ninside a building."},{"time":799080,"text":"So if you can have folding and autonomy,"},{"time":802680,"text":"you can do that\nin one-seventh of the space."},{"time":805120,"text":"That goes down to 10,000 dollars per car,"},{"time":807320,"text":"just for the cost of the parking."},{"time":808920,"text":"You add shared use,\nand you can even go further."}]},{"cues":[{"time":812880,"text":"We can also integrate\nall kinds of advanced technology"},{"time":815960,"text":"through this process."},{"time":817200,"text":"There's a path to market\nfor innovative companies"},{"time":820360,"text":"to bring technology into the home."},{"time":822040,"text":"In this case, a project\nwe're doing with Siemens."},{"time":824640,"text":"We have sensors on all\nthe furniture, all the infill,"},{"time":827240,"text":"that understands where people are\nand what they're doing."},{"time":829960,"text":"Blue light is very efficient,"},{"time":831680,"text":"so we have these tunable\n24-bit LED lighting fixtures."},{"time":835840,"text":"It recognizes where the person is,\nwhat they're doing,"},{"time":840000,"text":"fills out the light when necessary\nto full spectrum white light,"},{"time":844240,"text":"and saves maybe 30, 40 percent\nin energy consumption, we think,"},{"time":850480,"text":"over even conventional\nstate-of-the-art lighting systems."},{"time":855960,"text":"This just shows you the data\nthat comes from the sensors"},{"time":859400,"text":"that are embedded in the furniture."},{"time":861120,"text":"We don't really believe in cameras\nto do things in homes."},{"time":863960,"text":"We think these little wireless sensors\nare more effective."}]},{"cues":[{"time":867960,"text":"We think we can also personalize sunlight."},{"time":870240,"text":"That's sort of the ultimate\npersonalization in some ways."},{"time":872931,"text":"So we've looked at articulating\nmirrors of the facade"},{"time":875920,"text":"that can throw shafts of sunlight\nanywhere into the space,"},{"time":879840,"text":"therefore allowing you\nto shade most of the glass"},{"time":882240,"text":"on a hot day like today."},{"time":884480,"text":"In this case, she picks up her phone,"},{"time":886360,"text":"she can map food preparation\nat the kitchen island"},{"time":890960,"text":"to a particular location of sunlight."},{"time":893400,"text":"An algorithm will keep it in that location\nas long as she's engaged in that activity."},{"time":898600,"text":"This can be combined\nwith LED lighting as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":902760,"text":"We think workplaces should be shared."},{"time":904880,"text":"I mean, this is really\nthe workplace of the future, I think."},{"time":907714,"text":"This is Starbucks, you know."},{"time":909234,"text":"Maybe a third --"},{"time":910440,"text":"And you see everybody\nhas their back to the wall"},{"time":912720,"text":"and they have food and coffee down the way"},{"time":914744,"text":"and they're in their own\nlittle personal bubble."},{"time":917200,"text":"We need shared spaces\nfor interaction and collaboration."},{"time":919920,"text":"We're not doing a very good job with that."},{"time":922160,"text":"At the Cambridge Innovation Center,\nyou can have shared desks."},{"time":926240,"text":"I've spent a lot of time in Finland\nat the design factory of Aalto University,"},{"time":930960,"text":"where the they have a shared shop\nand shared fab lab, shared quiet spaces,"},{"time":935680,"text":"electronics spaces, recreation places."}]},{"cues":[{"time":939840,"text":"We think ultimately,\nall of this stuff can come together,"},{"time":943320,"text":"a new model for mobility,\na new model for housing,"},{"time":947040,"text":"a new model for how we live and work,"},{"time":949360,"text":"a path to market\nfor advanced technologies."},{"time":952200,"text":"But in the end, the main thing\nwe need to focus on are people."},{"time":955129,"text":"Cities are all about people."},{"time":956720,"text":"They're places for people."},{"time":958760,"text":"There's no reason\nwhy we can't dramatically improve"},{"time":961240,"text":"the livability and creativity of cities"},{"time":963560,"text":"like they've done in Melbourne\nwith the laneways"},{"time":967480,"text":"while at the same time\ndramatically reducing CO2 and energy."},{"time":972080,"text":"It's a global imperative.\nWe have to get this right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":975440,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":976680,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}